cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY

The paper discusses the use of Altmetric.com scores to predict future citation counts, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the management and analysis of scholarly publications. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it deals with the retrieval and analysis of information from various sources. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are also possible categories as they deal with the analysis of social networks and software impact. Finally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper discusses the non-scholarly impact of research.
